		</div>
		<div class=" col-md-7 item">
			<h4 class="HeadingG"> What does the visualization mean?</h4>
			<ul class="foobar789"> 
				<li class="foobar789"> Grey dots represent one or more participants in the conversation</li>
				<li class="foobar789"> Participants are closer together if they tend to agree, and further apart if they tend to disagree.</li>
				<li class="foobar789"> Each participant sees their own position in the conversation as a blue dot that moves with each vote.</li>
				<li class="foobar789"> Shaded grey areas represent opinion groups. Participants within an opinion group tend to agree with others in that group.</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="foobar789"> A participant is counted as 'in the conversation' if they have reacted to enough comments (either 7 comments or 100% of comments, whichever comes first). Excluding those who didn't heavily participate improves the reliability of the statistical analysis. However, those participants who are not yet 'in the conversation' will still see a blue dot representing their position in the conversation.</p>
		</div> 
		<div class=" col-md-7 item">
			<h4 class="HeadingG">Groups </h4>
			<p class="foobar789"> By clicking on a group, you can see the comments which are most representative of that group's opinion. Specifically, these comments are generally agreed upon within the selected group, but disagreed upon outside the group. </p>
		</div>
